column10:
Fun and exciting open-world FPS set on the fictional Rook Islands. This game skyrocketed the franchise to the moon (for better or for worse) and set standards and templates that can still be seen in the modern gaming industry. I have no nostalgia, this is my first time playing this game and most of its elements still hold up, so I can easily recommend it if you don't mind games with tons of collectibles and a somewhat repetitive gameplay loop.

Pros:
- Awesome arsenal with customisation;
- Memorable characters;
- Great visuals;
- Awesome writing;
- Good driving;
- Fun stealth;
- Great sense of progression;
- Compelling story;
- Great gunplay;
- Good optimisation;
- Vaas is one of the most memorable and charismatic villains (criminally underused BTW);
- Great sound design and soundtrack;
- Responsive controls;
- Good AI;
- Amazing voice acting;
- Good environmental storytelling;

Cons:
- Most side missions are boring;
- Anticlimactic boss fights with QTE;
- Very strong ludonarrative dissonance in the beginning;
- Second half of game loses a lot of steam;
- Gameplay loop can get repetitive;
- Ubisoft Connect(Upaly) is complete garbage;

No Achievements and No trading cards ;-;
No cloud saves aswell...
Also ubisoft launcher, WTF?!
